{"cursor":"5583","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":":This article is for the Egyptian-Canadian professor. For other uses of the name\nsee [[Al-Badawi]]. {{Infobox person |occupation = preacher, professor, public\nspeaker, writer |color = |image = |image_size = |caption = |alt = |name = Jamal\nBadawi |birth_date = |death_date = |religion = Islam |main_interests = Islamic\nDawah |notable_ideas = |influences = Hasan Al-Banna |influenced = |signature =\n| website = [http://sobey.smu.ca/biographies/faculty/jamal-badawi.html SMU\n| faculty page]\n}}\n\n'Jamal A. Badawi' () is an Egyptian born Muslim Canadian former professor in the\nSobey School of Business, Saint Mary's University in Halifax, Nova Scotia. He is\nan author, preacher and speaker on Islam.\n\nHe completed his undergraduate studies at Ain Shams University in Cairo, Egypt.\nHe left for the U.S. in the 1960s and completed his Masters and doctorate, both\nin the department of Business Administration, at Indiana University in\nBloomington, Indiana. [http://www.institutealislam.com/scholars-introduction-dr-jamal-\nbadawi/ Scholars Introduction: Dr. Jamal Badawi] He has been serving as a\nvolunteer imam of the local Muslim community in the Halifax Regional\nMunicipality since 1970. He cites Hassan al-Banna and Muslim Brotherhood as his\nsource for inspiration. [http://www.emel.com/article?id=5&a_id=1516 On Mount Nur with Dr Jamal\nBadawi]\n\nIn addition to his participation in lectures, seminars and interfaith dialogues\nin North America, Badawi was invited as a guest speaker in various functions\nthroughout the world. He is also active in several Islamic organizations,\nincluding the Canadian Council on American-Islamic Relations, the Fiqh Council\nof North America (FCNA), the Muslim American Society (MAS), and the European\nCouncil for Fatwa and Research (ECFR). [http://www.pointdebasculecanada.ca/article/1400-who-is-behind-the-\nislamic-school-being-planned-for-west-edmonton.php Who Is Behind The Islamic\nSchool Being Planned For West Edmonton?] He is also a member of the\nIslamic Society of North America (ISNA) and the founder and chairman of the\nIslamic Information Foundation, a non-profit foundation seeking to promote a\nbetter understanding of Islam and Muslims towards non-Muslims. He has lectured\nextensively in North America and abroad, and speaks on a variety of topics\nincluding Islam and Christianity and is a guest scholar at The American Learning\nInstitute for\nMuslims. [http://www.alimprogram.com/overview/introduction.shtml The\nAmerican Learning Institute for Muslims]\n\nBadawi has authored several books and articles on Islam. He also researched,\ndesigned and presented a 352-segment television series on Islam, aired in\nCanada, the US and other countries. [http://www.isna.net/ISNAHQ/pages/Dr-Jamal-A-\nBadawi.aspx Islamic Society of North America] Audio and video copies of\nthis series are widely available.\n\nBadawi is married and the father of five children.\n","linknr":146,"url":"Jamal_Badawi","recorded":1375078000,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Jamal_Badawi&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Jamal_Badawi&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Al-Badawi","/wiki/Preacher",